Group Name: Exploding Head Computer Levitating Men

1. Availability for meeting expectations
Be available for meetings at given times. 24 hr. Aavance notice if you're not able to make a meeting.
Things happen, people are sick etc., follow up with minutes taker if you miss a meeting to echange information.
If 2 meetings are missed without notice and no follow-up, proceed to the not meeting expectations section, point 6.

2. Response time to communication expectations
Within approximately 6 hours on a weekday.
Within approximately 12 hours on a weekend.

3. Definition of done: when is a task complete? (hint: "I'm done with that but I didn't check it in to github" is not done.)
Task is complete, code is checked into github, and code is reviewed by 2 or more group members.

4. Scrum meeting format/frequency and distribution of documentation tasks (meeting minutes, updating task board)
In person (ideally) After class Tuesday/Thursday at 10:20
Virtual meeting/check in noon on Sunday.
Mitchell will be in charge of meeting minutes; if Mitchell is not available Sam will take minutes.
Updating task board should fall on the individual; update the board when you accept, complete a task etc.

5. Procedure for adopting policies (e.g. code style, code check-in steps, documentation updates) 
Utilize built-in PyCharm style format.
Code check-in: Move task to "Code Review Needed" and post in Discord code-reviews channel.
Simple majority vote to adopt/change policy.

6. Procedure for handling a member who is not meeting expectations:
 a. must include at least 3 actions before involving the instructor
 1. 1 on 1 discussion with group member.
 2. Group intervention with group member.
 3. Discussion with group and TA (scrum master).

7. Signatures: each member must sign their name by typing their name at the bottom of the document.
